RDD concept

RDD - resilient distributed dataset

  • collection of objects spread across a cluster, stored in RAM or Disk
  • built through parallel transformation
  • automatically rebuilt on failure


    Transformations: f(RDD)=> RDD
  • lazy
  • e.g.¬†map, filter, groupBy

    Actions
  • trigger computation
  • e.g.¬†collect, save, count

DataFrames

  • RDD + schema
  • faster implementation
  • execution lazy, query optimizer
    by databricks
  • join/filter

RDD vs.¬†DataFrames - code

  #spark.yarn.queue = 'mi_prod', 
  spark.executor.memory = '2g',
  spark.executor.instances = '20',
  spark.yarn.driver.memoryOverhead = '1024', 
  spark.yarn.executor.memoryOverhead = '1024', 
  spark.driver.extraJavaOptions='-XX:MaxPermSize=1024m'#512m' 
)

RDD in SparkR

  • old sparkR docs: https://amplab-extras.github.io/SparkR-pkg/rdocs/1.2/index.html
  • wordCount
#pyspark: wordcounts = words.map(lambda s: (s, 1)).reduceByKey(lambda a, b : a + b).collect()
words <- SparkR:::parallelize(sc,c("hello", "world", "goodbye", "hello", "again"))
pairs <- SparkR:::map( words,function(word){ list(word,1L)} )
res <- SparkR:::reduceByKey(pairs,"+",2L)
res2 <- SparkR::collect(res)
